sentences: Gholām-Hossein Banān (Persian: غلامحسين بنان‎; 5 May 1911 – 27 February 1986) was an Iranian musician and singer.
One of the most prominent Iranian singers of the 20th century, he was renowned for the quality of his voice.
His mother was related to the ruling Qajar dynasty of Iran; she was the daughter of Mohammad Taqi Mirza Rokn ed-Dowleh, a brother of Naser al-Din Shah Qajar (r. 1848–1896).
Banān joined the Iranian National Music Association in 1942, and appeared on Iranian National Radio that same year.

In 1957 or 1958, Banān became blind in his right eye following a car accident.
Banān died 7:00 pm on Thursday 27 February 1986 in Iranmehr Hospital in Gholhak, Tehran.
